Restrict scope of variables

This patch makes two helper variables, each used only on one or two lines,
local to those lines.  This makes the code easier to understand, because it
is now obvious that these variables are not used elsewhere.  It also might
enable some compilers to optimize the code more effectively.

2001-10-07  Michael Ernst  <mernst@alum.mit.edu>

	* src/decl.cpp (ProcessFieldDeclaration): Restrict scope of helper
	variables used to set field_type.

diff -u -r --exclude=*~ --exclude=*.o --exclude=jikes src/decl.cpp ../jikes-1.15-patched/src/decl.cpp
--- src/decl.cpp	Fri Sep 28 21:12:19 2001
+++ ../jikes-1.15-patched/src/decl.cpp	Sun Oct  7 15:37:08 2001
@@ -2669,9 +2669,13 @@
